    "text": "Rest days don't automatically buy a high score — recovery tracks what your body did overnight, not whether you trained. Two things stand out in today's inputs. First, sleep: 6.1 h against a 7.6 h need, a gap of about 1.5 h, which is the largest single shortfall in your data. Second, your HRV of 46 ms is about 5 ms below its 30-day baseline of 51 ms. Your journal has a late-caffeine tag for yesterday, and late caffeine often lines up with shorter, shallower sleep — an association worth testing, not a proven cause. Everything else looks unremarkable: resting heart rate 60 bpm versus a 58 bpm 30-day mean is a small move. Tonight's lever: cut caffeine off by mid-afternoon and aim your bedtime at the full 7.6 h.",
